# T1136.001 - Create Account: Local Account

**MITRE ATT&CK Technique:** [T1136.001](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1136/001/)

**Tactic:** Persistence

**Objective:** Create a local user account on Windows 10 to simulate persistence and backdoor access commonly used by adversaries.

## Attack Attempts Summary

### 1. Attempt from Kali Linux (Remote Account Creation)
**Tools tried:**
- Impacket (`wmiexec.py`, `psexec.py`)
- Custom PowerShell / net user commands sent remotely
- Simple host script for payload delivery

**Issues Encountered:**
- Commands failed to execute reliably
- Permission errors or connection issues
- Account creation did not succeed remotely

**Troubleshooting Done:**
- Tried different Impacket modules and command encoding
- Used `-ExecutionPolicy Bypass`
- Tested basic remote connectivity via SSH and WMI
- Enabled necessary firewall rules

**Result:** Failed after multiple attempts. Remote account creation via Impacket was unreliable in this lab environment.

### 2. Successful Method: Atomic Red Team (Local Execution)

**Command Used:**
```powershell
# Run all tests for T1136.001
Invoke-AtomicTest T1136.001

# Or run specific tests
Invoke-AtomicTest T1136.001 -TestNumbers 4   # Create a new user in PowerShell (Windows)
Invoke-AtomicTest T1136.001 -TestNumbers 5   # Create a new user via net.exe (Windows)
